SIMPLE: mantelet
RECORDS: 1

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Mantelet
<hw>Man"tel*et</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[F., dim. of
<ets>manteau</ets>, OF. <ets>mantel</ets>. See <er>Mantle</er>.]</ety>
<sn>1.</sn> <sd>(a)</sd> <def>A short cloak formerly worn by
knights.</def> <sd>(b)</sd> <def>A short cloak or mantle worn by
women.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>A <qex>mantelet</qex> upon his shoulders hanging.</q>
<rj><qau>Chaucer.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <fld>(Fort.)</fld> <def>A musket-proof shield of rope,
wood, or metal, which is sometimes used for the protection of sappers or
riflemen while attacking a fortress, or of gunners at embrasures; -- now
commonly written <asp>mantlet</asp>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><-- p. 893 --></p>

<p><ent>Mantelletta</ent>⟦br⟧
